Twelve main roads in Hull are to be resurfaced after showing signs of deterioration, the city council said.The work will be carried out during off-peak hours or overnight.Most will be done as "mobile works" by closing individual lanes, but some roads will be fully closed.The work will take place between 1 July and 10 July, excluding the weekend of July 6-7.
Hull City Council said defects and cracks would be filled before the road surfaces were sealed.Letters are being sent to residents giving information about any access restrictions.There will be diversions put in place when roads are closed, the council said.The work schedule is:Follow BBC East Yorkshire on Facebook, X (formerly Twitter), and Instagram. Send your story ideas to eastyorkslincs.news@bbc.co.uk
